review_blob: Hazy lager drinks well,a bit creamy and very nice outdoors wirh the caribe breeze. On tap at Totem bar
beer_name: Old Harbor Santo Viejo Lager Pilsner

review_blob: Yes it isnt a balls-out Rauch beer...nice as an intro to the concept - understated .  Flavorful, a nice mouth explosion (yes a panzer reference) but like the Nazis it doesnt last.  Its a seasonal so try it if you see it.  The 10 oz pours st ale house Columbia rock for tasting.  Especially if you accidentally order the blonde for your girlfriend

Solid mild beer...Thats what its supposed to be.  Nice winter session beer ala wood burning stove... A bit of smoke on the nose, malt comes thru nicely clean and simple.  Perhaps a bit aggressively carbonated.  Intrigued to try in cask.  Why is it OK to have session/ day time IPA s but for those of us who do not want to be constantly choked with hops this is a good choice.
Had on cask in Dallas.  Smooth with nut flavors well balanced with malt.  Surprising light drinking for its complexity.  Its a cool night in Big D and this sits very well

Wow. Tasted in bottle in mid September in Baltimore.  Has lively end of year holiday overtones...especially at 12%! Lots o vanilla ala holiday cookies, marzipan (almond paste) from German pastries  spicy from oak and sweet caramel loveliness.  Will put away some bottles for holiday cheer!
Very different bpa.  Taste resembles a pilsner.  Must be the champagne yeast.  crisp and refreshing, seems lighter than 6.5 abv.  Pleasant lingering finish like a geisha coffee.

Well its a beer you salivate for if you like a simcoe beauty contest.  I do and this is the perfect vessel to showcase the hop as no doubt intended.  Ive had this in bottle but this one on tap and deliciously served at punks in Annapolis MD.

Nice peat 
finish....feels like that happy warm feeling after drinking single malt Scotch after the alcohol has dissipated.  Surprisingly complex looks unassuming

On the finish a lovely dunkel...the nose is too wort-ish for my taste.  Toffee, I think not coffee as others have commented.  All in all a lively beer on a coolish summer night hearkening to the coming Oktoberfest beers of September... a nice gateway drug
Too much toffee character.  If youre a fan of flavored coffees then this might appeal to you.
Had this at ladyface...sadly, even though other LF beers are excellent this one not worth a wit.  Flat lemonade taste.  Try a sample before you commit...

Well balanced with nice, but not overwhelming, rye bread taste.  Very pale head and a bit cloudy ....drinking it at the brew pub in Agoura ...very nice beer to drink outside in the transition when the hot day cools rapidly in the hills near sunset

Amazing take in California of the German classic with low ibu ....nice for a change from pervasively hoppiness on the west coast.  Well done maltiness very toady.  Having it at LAB in agoura hills on tap.  My Indian associates deScription is brewed beer tea!
Sensual and balanced...a grand dame in a dance of flashy adolescents these days...old school.  Pleasantly malty and complex lovely toasted golden color

Nice light dark lager but without the malty complexities of the true German.  That said a wonderful late night summer beer when the air has cooled and the tinge of autumn and Oktoberfest is in the air.
beer_name: Heavy Seas / Devils Backbone Land Ho! Black Pilsner Style Lager

review_blob: Nice malty sweet dopplebock. roasted chocolate honey notes. Slight alcohol finish. Ones enough. Let it warm up and youre good to go.
Nice pilsner over all.  A little sweeter maltier than others Ive had.  An above average baseball beer.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Excellent doppelbock.  Sweet balanced caramel roasty fireside brew.  German alps basking on a bearskin rug.
Nice showcase of the Chinook from bitterness to aroma.  Not too bitter that the malt is obscured hence the imperial.  Very dangerous beer at 10%.
beer_name: Flying Dog Imperial IPA - Chinook Single Hop

review_blob: Interesting.  On cask at Max?s in Baltimore home of Oliver?s.  Very smooth creamy and sweet on finish with a splash of bitterness in between.
Drinking on tap at maxs baltimore.  Straight forward wild yeast flavor.  A lot of citrus with a moderate bitterness. Sweet finish.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Tank 7 Farmhouse Ale

review_blob: On draft at Maxs in Baltimore...stunning beer, best of Maxs very extensive draft list.
beer_name: Firestone Walker Wookey Jack Black Rye IPA

review_blob: Drinking cask version at heavy seas in Baltimore.... far superior to also on draft version.  Tasting both side by side.  Both have same characteristic aroma/flavoring hop presence but the cask is noticeably less bitter allowing more of the malt flavor through.
Dark sweet malt taste.  Good head retention.  Clear fruit presence, most notably cherry. Slight hop flavors.  Moderate alcohol finish.
Dark and smooth with roasted chocolate notes.  Rich, sweet malt flavor. Light bitterness and carbonation.
Silky smooth.  Touch of bourbon with little to no alcohol on the nose, more noticeable on the finish.  Poured in pint glass.
beer_name: DuClaw Bourbon Barrel X-1 (Imperial Chocolate Rye Porter)
